column5: Only 4 inches of ice so no vehicles of any kind. I won't be out there til the huts are out.         dsn
dang - shoulda gone today -  next Saturday for sure
damn, dont think i'll be going to cooks on sat, i'll head to a smaller lake, hopefully no one.. haha
Yeah next Saturday should be better if the temps get colder throughout the week!! Which it looks like it will so far. But I won't be out til the huts are. I like the warmth.
yup  next saturday is looking good
My goodness! It looks rather chilly up there! I don't know how y'all find the ponds in that snow covered cow pasture like that... maybe we'll see a couple reports tonight?
Next week will be a lot safer.... this weekend you will be a stat for going through the ice...  You gotta be plum deperate to go out when it ain't safe..."
thank god  the next 5 1/2 days are going to take forever
thanks for the update,and today i heard that scugog had alot of guys out on the lake,havnt heard any reports yet...but i should very soon
I wouldn't  worry  now about the ice. All those people tested it out. Suppose to stay cold, so it should thicken... big lake is frozen now. Hope it hold's.
nice to see but be careful
At least if someone went through theres lots of guys around to help you out.
